node.text: How to know if you are overthinking it? Best selling author Michelle Rial chats with me about her creative slump, the shower principle, how framing is important, and her new book that’s kinda sad but maybe a little funny, but mostly sad. I promise you will find humor and comfort in Michelle’s simple yet complex translations of what being human feels like. Follow her @michellerial

node.text: Kristin Neff, Ph.d. Goal is to be a compassionate mess. With decades of research, she talks about how how the energies of fierce and tender self-compassion come together to help us be true to ourselves. Find out more from @neffselfcompassion or take her self-compassion scale on self-compassion.org published by @harper_wave

node.text: For years I have been trying to fit emotions into one image. To locate something universally human. This year, I started a newsletter to explore the complex nature of thoughts and feelings, the things that are too complicated and messy to fit into one image - it’s called “bad at keeping secrets” it’s a newsletter with very little news. I hope it can be a conversation. That we can talk about what it feels like to be human in this moment.

node.text: Bay Area surface designer, printer, writer, educator, @jenhewett talks about letting go of perfectionism, how she worked through failure and learned to trust herself. She has a collection out now with @rubystarsociety and her newest book is coming out this fall. We also touch on her journey from majoring in English at UC berkeley to falling in love with screen printing. I am so grateful to get to share Jen’s amazing work with you.

node.text: Who do you feel this way for? How do you choose who to stay with and how to leave if you need to? Today, in my substack newsletter, I talk about the complexities of sticking by someone’s side and my ever changing ideas on the role of marriage in modern society. I quote @glennondoyle @alaindebotton and of course @kanyewest has something to say on the topic. Do you? I would love to hear about it. Tell me where u find the line between knowing when to stay or go?

node.text: Thinking of you.

node.text: Swipe right. I have been on both sides of this. Recently, I found myself hiding things from someone I love because I didn’t want them to feel bad. Do u do this? How can we recover? And sometimes, it’s really hard to force myself to be happy for others when I am down. Help!

node.text: Long-term thinking is so hard. Today, I am super lucky to get to go live with @katymilkman author of How To Change. Katy is a behavioral scientist at @whartonschool who has spent her life trying to help people make better choices for themselves. Ever wonder why you know that you need to exercise, but you just can't get yourself to do it? Katy has some ideas on how to trick your brain into making smart choices to elongate your life, literally. Published by @portfolio_books 9am pst

Renovators - Light up the future with Art and Tech. Has there been a time in your life when reality didn't add up to your expectations? I am inspired by how technology can help us be more creative and get in touch with our emotions. I use a tablet to make all my work. It allows me to express my thoughts and emotions rapidly - so I don't get slowed down by the medium. Waiting for paint to dry can be a drag.⁠ ⁠
✨Here is my entry for #OPPORenovators #IgniteTheLight2021 @oppo ! Now I challenge YOU to create your own version of Mona Lisa. Use whatever technology tools, software, spray print, filters. Check the link in bio for more.

node.text: I woke up this morning consumed with all the sadness that comes with being human. The scales of life swung to the “is all this pain and suffering worth it?” I am not saying that you should buy this mug. What I am saying is that after waking up and waking downstairs, talking to my dad and having a warm cup of coffee, life seemed manageable again. That the practice of finding little moments of joy is helpful to me. And if it feels right, maybe this might be a good time to try it. Or maybe, and I hope this is true, you are in the cycle of emotion of hope and joy already.
